 Architecture Components
1. Compute Layer


Amazon EC2 instances


Runs your web application



2. Load Balancer


Elastic Load Balancing


Distributes incoming traffic across multiple servers



3. Auto Scaling Group (ASG)


Maintains desired number of EC2 instances


Automatically adds/removes instances



4. Launch Template


Blueprint for EC2 instances


Includes:


AMI


Instance type


Security groups





5. Database Layer


Amazon RDS


Stores application data



6. Monitoring


Amazon CloudWatch


Tracks CPU, traffic, health



🔄 Workflow of the Project


User sends request


Load Balancer receives traffic


Traffic is distributed to EC2 instances


CloudWatch monitors CPU usage


Auto Scaling Group reacts:


High CPU → Launch new instances


Low CPU → Terminate extra instances





📈 Scaling Policies
🔹 Target Tracking


Maintain CPU at (e.g., 50%)


🔹 Step Scaling


Add/remove instances in steps


🔹 Scheduled Scaling


Scale based on time (e.g., peak hours)



